{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "procedure-setting-api-collection",
    "name": "ProcedureSetting API",
    "description": "API endpoints for managing Procedure Settings and their Steps\n\n**New:** Internal Procedure Settings (child rows under parent categories)\n- Each parent ProcedureSetting represents a category (employee_task, client_request, etc.)\n- Child internal procedures have a `form` key (start_task, extend_task_time, send_for_approval, etc.)\n- Each child has its own workflow steps, conditions, and ordering constraints\n\n**Base URL:** `{{url}}`\n**Auth:** Bearer token via `{{token}}` variable.\n\n**Variables:**\n- `procedure_setting_id` — Parent category ProcedureSetting ID\n- `step_id` — ProcedureSettingStep ID (integer)\n- `internal_procedure_setting_id` — Child internal procedure ID (UUID)\n\n**Collection Version:** 2.0.0 — Updated June 2026",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "url",
      "value": "http://localhost/api/v1",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "your-bearer-token-here",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "procedure_setting_id",
      "value": "parent-uuid-here",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "PARENT category ProcedureSetting UUID (e.g., the 'employee_task' row with parent_id = NULL)"
    },
    {
      "key": "step_id",
      "value": "1",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "ProcedureSettingStep ID (integer, not UUID)"
    },
    {
      "key": "internal_procedure_setting_id",
      "value": "child-uuid-here",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "CHILD internal procedure UUID (auto-generated when creating; use for Update/Delete and mobile app actions)"
    }
  ],
